BFN 

  [Text] The Bank for Reconstruction and Development has been 
set up under the Government of Kyrgyzstan. Its tasks are to 
support economic reforms and monitor the use of resources. 
Credits will be granted by it only for projects of state value. 
It will support small and medium scale businesses in the 
priority spheres of economy and take into consideration regional 
characteristics. Its authorized capital is 10 million soms. 

